-- Northam Mine Closure After Fatal Accident Cost It 7,000 Ounces of Platinum
-- Alastair Reed
-- 2010-07-30T09:03:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/northam-mine-closure-after-fatal-accident-cost-it-7-000-ounces-of-platinum.html

          
          
             Northam Platinum Ltd. said the
closure of its Zondereinde mine in South Africa following a
fatal accident cost it about 7,000 ounces of lost production.  
 Production resumed at the night shift yesterday, it said.  
          
          


  


        